article.headline: Duquesne 98, St. Bonaventure 80
article.story: OLEAN, N.Y. -- Bill Clark scored 24 points, leading Duquesne to a 98-80 win over St. Bonaventure on Saturday. Aaron Jackson scored 20 points, while Melquan Bolding scored 16. Eric Evans chipped in 14 points for the Dukes (11-4, 2-0 Atlantic 10), while Jason Duty added 13. Andrew Nicholson scored 18 points and grabbed eight rebounds for the Bonnies (10-5, 1-1). Jonathan Hall added 14 and had six assists. Tyler Benson scored 10 points. Duquesne never trailed, taking a 44-32 halftime lead after a 10-0 run. Duquesne shot 50 percent from the field and was 13-of-27 on 3 pointers. St. Bonaventure shot 45.9 percent from the field and was 6-of-16 from beyond the arc.
